{
  "texts": [
    "This approach enables LLMs to gradually align with complex human values through training based on a broad corpus of text data (Lambert et al., 2022), without having to either achieve AGI or fixate on ANI.",
    "Various philosophical theories have been applied to the alignment of LLMs, including the Rule-of-Thumb (Sun et al., 2023; Ziems et al., 2022) and the Veil of Ignorance (Weidinger et al., 2023).",
    "Despite these efforts, the theoretical foundation underlying OpenAI's AI alignment work remains unclear.",
    "Upon examining OpenAI's technical roadmap and conducting further tests on their relatively smaller models of GPT-2 and GPT-3, we discovered that OpenAI's training approach is similar to John Dewey's philosophy of the moral development of human beings through the cultivation of habits via training.",
    "Unlike traditional ethical theories such as utilitarianism and deontology, Dewey's moral philosophy emphasizes moral learning and habituation from social experience and practice.This closely corresponds with the behaviorist approach in contemporary AI development, where capabilities are progressively achieved through environmental feedback (Brooks, 1991; Mitchell, 2019; Sutton & Barto, 2018)."
  ]
}